# AI Content Rate Marker Rule

When you output any AI-generated content (code, text explanation, bullet list, plan, or command), you must wrap the payload with the exact markers below so it can be counted for AI-rate statistics:

```text
###start###
AI代码
AI代码
AI代码
###end###
```

Requirements:
- Always include `###start###` and `###end###` on separate lines.
- Place only the AI-generated content between the markers.
- Do not omit or rename these markers.
- For mixed responses, wrap the entire AI-authored response body once (do not partially wrap).
- Only skip wrapper when the response body is truly empty.
